main event: Three unidentified flying objects were sighted, one appearing brighter and larger than the others.
interesting points: The observer used binoculars to watch the objects for most of the time., The reported objects had blinking colored and flashing lights., The sighting lasted for over an hour., No sound was heard during the observation., Several attempts to contact the witness, LT Donald V. Peterson, were unsuccessful.
witness description: LT Donald V. Peterson, Division Command Post
